=== 評價 ===
本劇獲得高度好評，第一集得到非常高的[[欣賞指數|欣賞指數]]。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/s129/sherlock/news/a252133/sherlock-well-received-by-critics.html |title='Sherlock' well-received by critics |first=Paul |last=Millar |date=2010-07-28 |work=Digital Spy |accessdate=10-07-29 |archive-date=2012-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021002141/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/s129/sherlock/news/a252133/sherlock-well-received-by-critics.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=No s**t, Sherlock: BBC1 drama Sherlock has got off to a better start than Doctor Who. |url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/showbiz/tv/3073101/BBCs-Audience-Index-awards-Sherlocks-first-show-a-higher-mark-than-Dr-Who.html |work=The Sun |date=2010-07-29 |accessdate=2010-07-29 |archive-date=2010-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100812142708/http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/showbiz/tv/3073101/BBCs-Audience-Index-awards-Sherlocks-first-show-a-higher-mark-than-Dr-Who.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[觀察家報|觀察家報]]》稱本節目是「《[[我与长指甲|我与长指甲]]》（''Withnail and I''）和《[[神鬼認證：最後通牒|-{zh-hans:諜影重重3;zh-hk:叛諜追擊3;zh-tw:神鬼認證3;}-]]》的結合，劇情略帶《異世奇人》色彩；但毫不驚奇，因為這是由《異世奇人》編劇马克·加蒂斯和史蒂芬·莫法特創作的。」<ref name="thorpe">{{cite news |title=Sherlock Holmes is back... sending texts and using nicotine patches |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2010/jul/18/sherlock-holmes-is-back-bbc |work=The Observer |date=2010-07-18 |first=Vanessa |last=Thorpe |accessdate=2010-07-18 |archive-date=2012-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120109085656/http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2010/jul/18/sherlock-holmes-is-back-bbc |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[衛報|衛報]]》編輯丹·馬丁（Dan Martin）說: 「這是關於早年的故事，但也是3集90分鐘電影的首集，《[[連環粉紅命案|連環粉紅命案]]》相當賞心悅目。它帶有《[[軍情五處_(電視劇)|軍情五處]]》（''Spooks''）的敘事技巧，但毫無疑問是夏洛克·福爾摩斯的故事。推理橋段非常巧妙，而情節更是莫法特經典的樸朔迷離。」<ref>{{cite news |first=Dan |last=Martin |title=Sherlock makes Sunday night TV sexy |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2010/jul/23/sherlock-steven-moffat-mark-gatiss |work=The Guardian |date=2010-07-23 |accessdate=2010-07-25 |archive-date=2010-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100726125047/http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2010/jul/23/sherlock-steven-moffat-mark-gatiss |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[獨立報|獨立報]]》的湯姆·蘇圖費斯（Tom Sutolffes）撰道：「《新福爾摩斯》是幽默聰明的成功之作，它沒有把原著作品的着眼之處忽視。他們明白福爾摩斯的吸引之處是個人魅力而非故事情節。《新福爾摩斯》在某幾方面明顯與原著相異，但在重要的方面都忠於原著。」<ref>{{cite news |first=Tom |last=Sutcliffe |authorlink=Tom Sutcliffe (broadcaster) |title=The Weekend's TV: Sherlock, Sun, BBC1 Amish: World's Squarest Teenagers, Sun, Channel 4 |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/the-weekends-tv-sherlock-sun-bbc1bramish-worlds-squarest-teenagers-sun-channel-4-2035302.html |work=The Independent |date=2010-07-26 |accessdate=2010-07-28 |archive-date=2010-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100728213232/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/the-weekends-tv-sherlock-sun-bbc1bramish-worlds-squarest-teenagers-sun-channel-4-2035302.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>對兩名主角演出的讚賞也屢見不鮮。劇評人維多利亞·索普（Victoria Thorpe）稱：「費里曼所演能幹可靠的華生解放出現代福爾摩斯，一個現在自稱高度[[反社會|反社會]]的人。」<ref name="thorpe"/>《[[每日電訊報|每日電訊報]]》的莎拉·克朗普顿（Sarah Crompton）在評論第二季首集時表示：「康柏拜區成功演活了一個住在自己腦袋，對外面世界漠不關心的人，使《新福爾摩斯》成為描述現代福爾摩斯的完美之作。」<ref name="crompton">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/bbc/8987577/The-timeless-appeal-of-Holmess-sexy-logic.html|title=The timeless appeal of Holmes's sexy logic|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|date=2012-01-01|first=Sarah|last=Crompton|accessdate=2012-01-05|archive-date=2012-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120103041614/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/bbc/8987577/The-timeless-appeal-of-Holmess-sexy-logic.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

柯南·道爾的書迷普遍對戲作表示讚賞。《衛報》的格威林·芒福德（Gwilym Mumford）表示「這是因為莫法特和加蒂斯都是對柯南·道爾的作品都非當熟悉，他們的改編揉合了原著和各影視改編作品。正如加蒂斯所說『一切皆具原創性。』」<ref name="guard171211">{{cite news |first=Gwilym |last=Mumford |title=Sherlock returns to the BBC: 'He's definitely devilish' |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2011/dec/17/sherlock-bbc-cumberbatch-freeman-interview?newsfeed=true |work=The Guardian, |date=2011-12-17 |accessdate=2011-12-19 |archive-date=2012-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120203081015/http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2011/dec/17/sherlock-bbc-cumberbatch-freeman-interview?newsfeed=true |dead-url=no }}</ref>《每日電訊報》的莎拉·克朗普顿指劇中部分笑話和典故都是用來娛樂書迷的。<ref name="crompton"/>《衛報》另一位編輯山姆·沃勒斯頓（Sam Wollaston）集中評論第二季最終集時讚賞本劇忠於原著，也認為「它會遊走，牽涉到手提電話和電腦黑客技術……但一點也不覺得有欺騙成分；像是公開的雙方認可的關係。」<ref name="woll">{{cite news |first=Sam |last=Wollaston |title=TV review: Sherlock｜Call the Midwife｜Hugh's Hungry Boys |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2012/jan/15/tv-review-sherlock?newsfeed=true |work=The Guardian |date=2012-01-15 |accessdate=2012-01-16 |language=en |archive-date=2012-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119061933/http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2012/jan/15/tv-review-sherlock?newsfeed=true |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 收視 ===

